Weather analyst reveals the fact that Saudi Arabia was exposed to the tsunami
01 Nov 2019, 05:24 by Saeed Al Arabi
Said al-Arabi, weather analyst and weather expert Abdulrahman Raja, said that the heavy rain and "cold" Hafr al-Batin, which occurred a few days ago, is a historical case due to increased levels of tropical humidity in all layers of the atmosphere; confirming in his interview with "already" that he wrote a tweet In an interview to precede the fact that the east coast of Saudi Arabia was hit by tsunamis and tsunamis, he said: "Unexpected", adding: "Sometimes it affects a segment of society; but most segments of the population followers analysts and weather experts, They are knowledgeable and confident in some weather experts on social media sites He said that the reasons for the exposure of the sub-Batr days to heavy rain, and the fall of hail with large grains, described by weather experts as "historical" is a historical case due to increased tropical humidity in all layers of the atmosphere, and the presence of cold air At low pressures at this time of the year a severe rainy condition occurred, and a tweet was written alerting several days before the situation. He continued that atmospheric changes were actually caused by the extreme warming of the surrounding seas such as the Arabian Sea, the Indian Sea, the Red Sea, and increased atmospheric humidity. We now notice in early November that we will see my case Two orbits in the Arabian Sea at the same time, therefore, the increase in the extremism of cases in the next few years is not ruled out;
